<br>
guild tagging - list who has this option.. Inform a main person  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Tagging officer </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. The TO posts the new guildies information in the designated area's and updates the member lists. If the tagging person tags and does not inform Tagging Officer then strip them from tagging. If the TO can not handle posting the info, replace them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ally person</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - This person is in constant connection with the allied guild representative. This person will find out when their raids or events are and post them if GC is invited to attend. This person will also inform the allied guilds when GC has a raid or event they are invited to attend.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raid coor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - This person's job should be to schedule a raid (ALL LEVELS). Once this person schedules a raid. It is posted on GC raid board.. time/date/place/levels .. This person then informs the ally person so that they can contact the allied guilds, if they are invited to attend. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Fun Coor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This person is responsible for scheduling maybe one fun inter-action day a month. Rather it be GC only, GC and allied guilds or open to all. This person posts information on GC boards. Then gets with the ally person, so they can  contact the allied guilds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Treasurer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This person should know a bit about items, if they are worth selling to guildies or selling them to a vendor and keeping track of the GC raid kitty. The raid kitty is for raid materials: stones, port stone things, dots, and coffins ect. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raid grouper </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> person makes groups for raids. The group structure is out-lined somewhere by Oog. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raid loot person </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This person knows GC loot rules. This person handles announcing loot rules at raids (the major ones) ex. merited items/last pieces/epic pieces/ML/ money item collector. This person will be the person on the said raid to contact when loot is to be randomed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Raid money collector</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This person will hold all money and money items dropped on the raid. This person will distribute money at the end of the raid to replace gems used. Make sure gems are being used. This person will sell all money items, if this person is not the treasurer then the collector will then get with the treasurer and put the money in the guild kitty.<br>
<br>
Post or re-post GC loot rules, if they have changed.<br>
Post or re-post GC raid rules, if they have changed.<br>
Post or re-post charter, if it has changed.<br>
Post or re-post guilding polices, if this has changed.<br>
Post or re-post recruiting polices, if this has changed.<br>
<br>
all I can think of at this moment...These in my eyes are simple things to take care of. They can be assigned and completed in a very short amount of time. But like I said these are my opinions and suggestions, I leave the rest up to GL and the officers of GC.. Maybe post something you are interested in, so that those in charge have an idea with their titles and descriptions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/utiifaalokhart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tiifaa lokhart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/29/01 7:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p076.ezboard.com/fgriffinclawmembersonly.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1596.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My suggestion for GC</span><hr size=1> what are the requirements for a member to be able to tag???<br>
